  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best Allo easter eggs?",
  "response": "Google Allo, the now-discontinued messaging app, had several fun Easter eggs and hidden features that users could discover. Here are some of the best ones:\n\n### 1. **Google Assistant Games**\n   - You could play games like **Movie Quiz**, **Song Quiz**, and **20 Questions** with Google Assistant.\n   - Just type \"Play [game name]\" or \"Let's play a game\" to trigger them.\n\n### 2. **Google Assistant Pranks**\n   - You could ask Google Assistant to prank your friends by calling them and playing funny messages. For example, type \"Prank call [friend's name]\" and choose from the available prank scenarios.\n\n### 3. **Special Responses to Certain Phrases**\n   - Google Assistant had playful responses to specific phrases like:\n     - \"Tell me a joke\"\n     - \"Do a barrel roll\"\n     - \"Who\u2019s your daddy?\"\n     - \"What\u2019s the meaning of life?\"\n     - \"Marco Polo\"\n     - \"Make me a sandwich\"\n     - \"Up, Up, Down, Down, Left, Right, Left, Right, B, A\" (the Konami code)\n\n### 4. **Special Effects in Conversations**\n   - Typing certain words or phrases would trigger special effects, such as animations or stickers. For example:\n     - \"It\u2019s raining\" or \"Rain rain go away\" would trigger rain animations.\n     - \"Happy birthday\" would trigger a birthday cake animation.\n     - \"Congratulations\" would cause balloons to float up the screen.\n\n### 5. **Magic wand for Emoji Customization**\n   - You could resize and move emojis in your messages using a \"magic wand\" tool. It allowed for creative and personalized emoji combinations.\n\n### 6. **Whisper and Shout Feature**\n   - Typing in **ALL CAPS** would make the text appear larger, and typing in lowercase would make it smaller, depending on the context.\n\n### 7. **Google Assistant\u2019s Personality**\n   - Google Assistant had a fun and quirky personality, responding to playful questions like:\n     - \"Are you Skynet?\"\n     - \"Do you love me?\"\n     - \"What\u2019s your favorite color?\"\n\n### 8. **Hidden Commands**\n   - Some hidden commands would trigger unique responses or actions, such as:\n     - \"Sing me a song\"\n     - \"Tell me a story\"\n     - \"What\u2019s your favorite movie?\"\n\nWhile Allo is no longer available, many of these Easter eggs and features have been integrated into Google Assistant on other platforms like Google Messages or Google Home devices.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
